testcase.name: Podam should not be able to create instances of an Abstract class even if the POJO has a full constructor
Podam should not create instances of non-instantiable classes
The management of external factories should be correct and chaining should work
Podam should not be able to create instances of an Abstract class if the external factory does not provide a concrete implementation
Podam cannot fill interface attributes if the external factory does not manufacture the right type
Podam should not create instances of an interface when given an external factory which does not manufacture the concrete type
Podam should fill POJOs and interface attributes if a full constructor sets the interface attribute value
